sentences: Neva Krysteva (Bulgarian: Нева Кръстева) (born 2 August 1946) is a Bulgarian organist, professor of music, pedagogue, composer from Moscow State Music Academy in Music Studies and Organ, and musicologist.
In 1978 she organized the first organ class in Bulgaria.
Her performing career in Bulgaria - her native country - starts in 1974, after the new pipe organ in Bulgaria Concert Hall in Sofia was installed.
